# START HERE — {{MODULE_NAME}}

> This file is a **human handoff**, not a Project Studio directive. It's written once
> at parent-setup time so any person (or new session) landing in this folder can get
> their bearings in under two minutes. If you're Claude: the machine-readable equivalent
> lives in `project-studio/module-seed.yaml`. Read that for structure; read this for
> narrative.

## What this folder is

**{{MODULE_NAME}}** is one module of the **{{PARENT_NAME}}** product. It lives in its own
folder and is managed as a standalone Project Studio project, but it coordinates with
sibling modules through a parent-level communication layer.

- **Purpose:** {{MODULE_PURPOSE}}
- **Role in the product:** {{MODULE_ROLE}}
- **Parent folder:** `{{PARENT_ABSOLUTE_PATH}}`
- **Created:** {{GENERATED_AT}}

## Where everything lives

```
{{MODULE_NAME}}/
├── CLAUDE.md                          ← Project Studio root index (module-local)
├── START-HERE.md                      ← you are here
├── project-studio/
│   ├── module-seed.yaml               ← auto-trigger resume seed (read by CoS)
│   ├── shared/
│   │   ├── shared-index.md            ← index of parent-shared assets (relative paths)
│   │   └── bus-snapshot.md            ← optional local view of recent bus entries
│   ├── inbox.md                       ← messages from siblings and parent
│   ├── outbox-staging.md              ← local drafts, delivered by `sync`
│   ├── team/                          ← module-scope personas + shared-persona overrides
│   ├── project/                       ← brief.md, roadmap.md, infrastructure/
│   ├── protocol/                      ← module boot/resume files
│   ├── registers/                     ← assumptions, risks, blockers, decisions
│   ├── log/                           ← turn logs and checkpoints
│   ├── imports/                       ← read-only context slices
│   └── archive/                       ← rotated logs and sealed messages
└── src/                               ← your code lives here
```

Parent-shared assets (brief, roadmap, brand, docs, conventions, data, parent- and
shared-scope personas) live under `{{PARENT_ABSOLUTE_PATH}}/.project-studio/shared/`
and `{{PARENT_ABSOLUTE_PATH}}/.project-studio/team/`. They are **referenced** from here
via relative paths in `project-studio/shared/shared-index.md`, **not copied**. If a
shared asset changes at the parent, a `shared-update` message will arrive in your
inbox — there is no silent auto-sync.

## What happens when you open a Claude session in this folder

1. Claude boots, reads `CLAUDE.md`, and detects `project-studio/module-seed.yaml`.
2. Detecting the seed auto-triggers **Module Resume Mode** (not the setup wizard).
3. CoS reads the seed, then the local protocol, then the inbox, then the roadmap.
4. CoS greets you with the current first active milestone and any unread messages.
5. Work proceeds inside this folder for the rest of the session.

If you want the setup wizard instead, delete `module-seed.yaml` (not recommended —
this will orphan the module from the parent). For the full resume flow, see
`project-studio/protocol/boot.md` and
`{{PARENT_ABSOLUTE_PATH}}/.project-studio/shared/` references.

## What crosses module boundaries (and what doesn't)

| Crosses boundaries                         | Stays local                           |
|--------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------|
| Messages via inbox / outbox / bus          | All code under `src/`                 |
| Shared assets (read-only, relative paths)  | Registers (assumptions, risks)        |
| Parent roadmap Tier 1 milestones           | Module roadmap Tier 2 milestones      |
| Parent- and shared-scope personas          | Module-scope personas                 |
| ADRs promoted to parent                    | Module-only ADRs                      |

CoS **never reads sibling module folders.** If you need information about a sibling,
send a `question` message via the outbox and run `sync`. The sibling's next session
will see it in their inbox.

## Common first actions

- **"What should I work on?"** — Ask CoS. It will open
  `project-studio/project/roadmap.md` and point at the first active milestone.
- **"Anything new from siblings?"** — Ask CoS to summarize the inbox.
- **"I need to tell payments about X."** — Ask CoS to draft an outbox message. Review
  it, then run `sync` to deliver.
- **"I forgot what we decided about X."** — Ask CoS to search
  `project-studio/registers/decisions.md` and, if relevant, the parent bus archive.
- **"I want a different persona on this."** — Ask CoS to swap the active persona or
  draft a per-module override for a shared persona.

